{{Quote|Sir, my diagnosis is sudden and massive calcification of your skeletal structure, of the rare type brought on by severely conductive exposure to electrical and other energy fields.|[[2-1B/Legends|2-1B]], to Luke Skywalker|<ref name="The Truce at Bakura">''[[The Truce at Bakura]]''</ref>}}
'''Calcification''' was the sudden, rapid deposition of minerals in the [[Blood/Legends|bloodstream]] onto [[Bone/Legends|bones]]. Side effects included dizziness, blurred vision, muscle spasms, and muscle weakness. [[Bacta tank/Legends|Bacta tank]] immersion or bed rest could cure it; if untreated, the affliction could become permanent. Calcification was caused by exposure to high-strength electric fields. It was also one of the after effects of exposure to [[Force lightning/Legends|Force lightning]]. After the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], where he confronted the [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Galactic Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], the fledging [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] was diagnosed with that disorder.

